  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://slack.rook.io/).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nThe operator adds a finalizer to the CephCluster so that when a cluster is deleted we can clean up the volumes before the cluster is stopped. Currently this check only happens for flex volumes in the [handleDelete()](https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/f7df86df16f75c25cf6195bcd8849beb399709e8/pkg/operator/ceph/cluster/controller.go#L757) method. \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nThe operator should check for volumes created by the csi driver and block the deletion if there are any active volumes.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\n<!-- Please let us know any circumstances for reproduction of your bug. -->\r\n- Create a ceph cluster\r\n- Create a csi rbd or cephfs volume\r\n- Delete the ceph cluster\r\n- See the csi volumes hang\r\n",
